<H1>UI design</H1><BR>
<OL>
  <LI>
  <P>Don't tie complex procedures to <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://cade.scope.edu/courseware/notes/mel/ui.html#immediate">imm=
ediate=20
  mode</A> controls.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Anticipate user mistake and allow graceful exit.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Use <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://cade.scope.edu/courseware/notes/mel/program.html#comment">=
comments</A>=20
  as procedure landmarks to facilitate maintenance of large scripts.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Show (through <A=20
  =
href=3D"file:///C:/AW/Maya4.0/docs/en_US/html/Commands/waitCursor.html">w=
aitCursor</A>,=20
  for example) a slow procedure's working.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Arrange parameters in decreasing order of importance, from left to =
right=20
  and from top to bottom.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Group related parameters together using <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://cade.scope.edu/courseware/notes/mel/ui.html#grplayout">fra=
meLayout=20
  or tabLayout</A>.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Parameter ranges and defaults should be consistent and =
reasonable.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Icons should be simple and markedly unique. Don't bother to =
illustrate the=20
  represented script's function.</P></LI></OL><BR>
<H2>General precaution</H2>
<OL>
  <LI>
  <P>Test complex procedures with small numbers.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Beware of memory shortage in long accumulated procedures. You can =
use <A=20
  =
href=3D"file:///C:/AW/Maya4.0/docs/en_US/html/Commands/flushUndo.html">fl=
ushUndo</A>=20
  and <A=20
  =
href=3D"file:///C:/AW/Maya4.0/docs/en_US/html/Commands/clearCache.html">c=
learCache</A>=20
  to reclaim memory, and <A=20
  =
href=3D"file:///C:/AW/Maya4.0/docs/en_US/html/Commands/memory.html">memor=
y</A>=20
  to check on memory availability.</P>
  <LI>
  <P>Use <A=20
  =
href=3D"file:///C:/AW/Maya4.0/docs/en_US/html/Commands/timerX.html">timer=
X</A>=20
  to time your script's execution.</P></LI></OL></BODY></HTML>

